          java.util.concurrent.ConcurrentHashMap<K,V> nodeCache
          Children in memory. The cache is necessary because the nodes are requested many times by the UI, and constructing them is an expensive operation since it may require disk access.

          java.util.ArrayList<E> rootChildren

        • surfaceStream

        • streams

          java.util.Map<K,V> streams
          Streams of branches being written. The key is the index of a root child whose descendants are being written. The stored value is a stream used to write there.

          The streams in this map satisfy the invariant that their cursors are inside of some branch (i.e. not in between of two consecutive branches).
